result.execSummary:
The defendant Allen R. Janke Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Arson of Building w/o Owner's Consent [Modifiers: Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.02(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: RESTITUTION INFORMATION

Defendant Allen R. Janke in court with attorney Ronald Gabriel Benavides.  Defendant Allen R. Janke in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
All parties have received the PSI and are prepared to proceed today.  
Atty Hendee makes sentencing arguments and recommends 10 years initial confinement followed by 3 years extended supervision with conditions.  State has complied with victim notification requirements.
Atty Benavides makes sentencing arguments and recommends 4 years initial confinement followed by 6 years extended supervision with conditions.
Defendant makes statement to the Court.
BY THE COURT:  Court sentences defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a period of 13 years.  Court orders 9 years Initial Confinement followed by 4 years Extended Supervision.  Sentence consecutive to any other sentence he is now serving.  Court grants 104 days credit for time served in the read-in case 14CF15.  
Conditions of Extended Supervision:  *Full-time employment.  *Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS Assessment and the Department of Corrections.  *Thinking for a Change Treatment (CGIP) if not completed prior to supervision.  *AODA treatment if not completed prior to sentencing.  *No contact with the victims or their residence.  *Psychological evaluation and compliance with any mental health treatment deemed necessary by evaluator and supervision agent.  *Pay costs of $268.00.  *Submit DNA sample if not already done and pay surcharge.  *Restitution in the amount of $38,033.84.
**Defendant is eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.

Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.
